sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / KServe Route
    participant API as OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Auth as Auth Middleware<br/>API Key Bearer
    participant Engine as vLLM Engine<br/>ZeroMQ IPC
    participant Worker as CPU Worker<br/>PyTorch + IPEX/OpenBLAS
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>PVC / S3 (443/TCP)
    participant Prom as Prometheus Scraper

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: OpenAI-Compatible Inference Request

    Client->>API: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS 8000/TCP<br/>Optional TLS
    API->>Auth: Validate API Key<br/>(if --api-key set)
    Auth-->>API: 401 Unauthorized / OK
    API->>Engine: Forward request<br/>ZeroMQ IPC (local)
    Engine->>Worker: Execute inference<br/>In-process function call

    Note over Worker,Storage: Model loaded at startup
    Worker->>Storage: Load model weights<br/>Filesystem (PVC) or HTTPS/443 (S3)<br/>TLS 1.2+ / IAM Auth
    Storage-->>Worker: Model artifacts

    Worker-->>Engine: Inference result
    Engine-->>API: Generated tokens<br/>(streaming SSE or batch)
    API-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>or SSE stream

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 2: TGIS gRPC Inference Request

    participant TGIS as TGIS gRPC Adapter<br/>8033/TCP gRPC

    Client->>TGIS: gRPC GenerationService<br/>8033/TCP plaintext
    TGIS->>Engine: Python call (in-process)
    Engine->>Worker: Execute inference
    Worker-->>Engine: Result
    Engine-->>TGIS: Generated text
    TGIS-->>Client: gRPC Response

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 3: Prometheus Metrics Collection

    Prom->>API: GET /metrics<br/>8000/TCP HTTP<br/>Optional TLS, No Auth
    API-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(latency, throughput, queue)
